# PokePon GitHub Pages deploy workflow

| | Production | Staging |
|---|---|---|
| URL | **https://pokepon.org** | **https://staging.pokepon.org** |
| Branch | `main` | `staging` |
| Deploy | `git push origin main` | `bash scripts/deploy-website-staging.sh` |

See `docs/WEBSITE_STAGING.md` and `.cursor/rules/staging-before-production.mdc`.

## When this applies

After website HTML/JS/CSS changes:

1. Work on **`staging`** branch; deploy with `bash scripts/deploy-website-staging.sh`.
2. Test on **https://staging.pokepon.org** with staging bot up.
3. Promote with `bash scripts/promote-website-to-production.sh` (merges to `main`, updates pokepon.org).

## Bot API vs site

- **Website** → UI only (staging site repo + `main` for production).
- **Poke-Cards** → `/api/*`; restart staging bot after API edits.

## Do not

- Push `main` for feature work before staging verification.
- Stop background bot/tunnel at the start of edits — restart staging bot when ready to test.
